      • getConverter

        protected Converter getConverter(YADAQueryResult yqr)
                          throws YADARequestException,
                                 YADAConverterException
        This method returns the appropriate converter Converter by looking first at the YADARequest.PS_CONVERTER parmater, if no class is set, or the class provided cannot be instantiated, the default converter is set using getDefaultConverter(YADAQueryResult)
        Parameters:
        yqr - the result container
        Returns:
        the appropriate Converter object
        Throws:
        YADARequestException - when the default converter cannot be instantiated
        YADAConverterException - when result reformatting fails

      • hasSingularQuery

        protected boolean hasSingularQuery()
        The yadaQueryResults array serves as a proxy for the queries being handled in the response. Since each YADAQuery object maps to a single YADAQueryResult this works out fine. Thus the method returns true if the yadaQueryResults array has a length = 1.
        Returns:
        true if the yadaQueryResults array has a length = 1

      • hasSingularResult

        protected boolean hasSingularResult()
        This method interrogates the yadaQueryResults array. If hasSingularQuery() returns true then the value at index 1 is checked. If this value is null or YADAQueryResult.hasSingularResult() returns true then this method returns true as well.
        Returns:
        true if the yadaQueryResults array contains a null value at it's first index or the result object contains only a single result set

      • hasMultipleResults

        protected boolean hasMultipleResults()
        Returns true if hasSingularResult() returns false and getHarmonyMap() returns null
        Returns:
        true if hasSingularResult() returns false and getHarmonyMap() returns null
